National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and officials from the National Security Council and State Department will be meeting with Chinese Communist Party Politburo Member Yang Jiechi in Rome. The purpose of the meeting is to maintain communication between the United States and China and discuss ongoing efforts to manage competition between the two countries. They will also discuss the impact of Russia's war against Ukraine on regional and global security. Additionally, Sullivan will meet with Luigi Mattiolo, Diplomatic Advisor to the Italian Prime Minister, to coordinate a strong international response to President Putin's actions.